# Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy

Last updated: June 12, 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how Poop Tracker ("we", "our", or "us") handles your information when you use our mobile application (the "App").

Information We Do Not Collect

Poop Tracker is designed with your privacy as a top priority. The App:

- Does NOT collect any personal information
- Does NOT require an account or registration
- Does NOT access the internet or require network permissions
- Does NOT send any data to external servers, APIs, or third parties
- Does NOT track your location, device identifiers, or usage patterns
- Does NOT use cookies, analytics, or tracking technologies of any kind
- Does NOT share any data with third parties

Data Storage

All information you enter into the App — including bowel movement logs, Bristol Stool Scale ratings, symptoms, notes, food tags, and preferences — is stored exclusively on your device using local storage (localStorage). No data is transmitted off your device at any time.

Data Export

You may choose to export your data as a CSV file. This file is generated locally on your device and saved to your device's storage. We have no access to exported data.

Data Deletion

Since all data resides on your device, you can delete it at any time by:
1. Clearing the app data through your device settings
2. Uninstalling the App
3. Using the data management options within the App settings

Children's Privacy

The App is not directed at children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect any information from children under 13.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the App. Your continued use of the App after any changes indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.

